  "instructions": [
    "Heat oil in a large Dutch oven over medium-high heat. Brown the lamb on all sides, then set aside.",
    "Add more oil if needed, then sauté onions until golden. Add garlic and cook for 1 minute.",
    "Stir in sweet chilli sauce, fermented lemon juice, ginger, cumin, cinnamon, turmeric, and salt. Cook for 1 minute.",
    "Add the browned lamb back to the pot, along with 1 cup of water. Cover and transfer to the oven.",
    "Braise for 2.5 hours or until the lamb is tender and falls apart easily.",
    "Skim off excess fat, then stir in chopped parsley.",
    "Serve the lamb with the sauce spooned over the top, garnished with additional parsley if desired."
  ],
